THE 5 TUTORIAL DESIGNS
(Most searched + most beginner-achievable — one image each)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
These five are the backbone of the tutorial section. Each needs a dedicated image.

DESIGN 1: Pastel French Tip (with coloured tip variation)
— Why: French tip is the single most searched nail look at-home; the 2026 version swaps white tip for blush, lavender, or butter yellow
— Difficulty: Beginner
— Estimated time: 25 min
— Key steps for writer: soft base coat, pastel tip colour applied with guide strip or tape, top coat to seal
— Image brief: Close-up of hands showing pastel-tipped nails (blush or lavender tip on nude base), natural lighting

DESIGN 2: Watercolour Floral (dot-method, no brush skill needed)
— Why: Floral is the top thematic request for Mother's Day nails; dot-method makes it beginner-safe without fine brushwork
— Difficulty: Beginner–Intermediate
— Estimated time: 35–40 min
— Key steps for writer: nude/soft base, diluted pink + green polish dabbed with dotting tool or toothpick in petal formation, green dot centre, clear top coat
— Image brief: Single nail close-up showing soft watercolour daisy or rose cluster on blush base

DESIGN 3: Heart Accent Nail
— Why: Heart designs dominate Mother's Day Pinterest boards and "mother's day nails DIY" TikTok — deeply searched, emotionally resonant
— Difficulty: Beginner
— Estimated time: 20 min
— Key steps for writer: single accent nail with two overlapping dots forming heart shape (dotting tool), all other nails solid nude or pink
— Image brief: Hand with one accent nail featuring a small pastel or red heart, remaining nails in coordinating nude

DESIGN 4: Pastel Ombré (two-colour sponge fade)
— Why: Ombré remains consistently popular for DIY; sponge method requires no professional tools
— Difficulty: Intermediate
— Estimated time: 40 min
— Key steps for writer: two pastel polish colours on makeup sponge, dab onto nail in overlapping strokes, multiple light layers, clean edges with brush + remover, top coat
— Image brief: Hands showing soft pink-to-lavender fade across nails, spring-light photography

DESIGN 5: Pearl Glaze / Soap Nail Effect
— Why: Pearl and glazed finishes are the #1 trending 2026 manicure style (confirmed across SERP, Hello Magazine, That Love Podcast research); soap nails are 2026's clean-girl aesthetic
— Difficulty: Beginner
— Estimated time: 15 min
— Key steps for writer: sheer nude or soft pink base, chrome powder pigment rubbed over dry nail with eyeshadow brush, sealed with glossy top coat — no UV lamp needed for this method
— Image brief: Close-up of hands with iridescent pearl-glazed nails, glossy finish catching light

